,Not Recommended,291010,18779803,"Posted: 30 October, 2015",all,Bizz,"Saw this game on sale for 19¢ and saw the game had generally positive reviews on Steam, so I decided to give it a shot.Graphics: D-. The first thing that stood out for me was how bad the graphics are. We're talking PS2-era graphics here, complete with low resution textures, poor lighting, the whole bit. It doesn't seem like a lot of effort was put into them. Especially with subtitles that use a basic Arial font with no style added to them whatsoever. But, graphics like these are typical in most Unity-based games and they did the job I guess.Sound: B+. Apart from the sound effect when picking up items (that sounds like someone hitting a Quarter against an empty bottle of Coke), the sound effects & music were both well done.Story: C-. Nothing fancy here, I won't go too far into it because of spoilers.Gameplay: C+. Apart from the first room which teaches you how to look for items (by listening for them), there is no other tutorial so to speak. The objective is to find all the pages to your Daughter's lost journal and to solve puzzles using certain items to get past obstructions. The rooms are randomly generated so there is no map, while this may make it confusing it ultimately doesn't matter, the game still progresses in linear fashion. I haven't quite figured out how to avoid Hat Man, but you'll know if he's close by when the screen flickers, your heart starts pounding, and the wind nearby sounds all distorted. As for scariness, I personally did not get too spooked even when getting caught my first time. In fact I was more♥♥♥♥♥♥♥♥off than anything. Results may vary for others, but for me it just didn't freak me out at all. Overall the game can be completed fairly quicky once you find out what to do (I suggest reading a walkthrough, it helps).Performance: C. It's a unity game, so don't expect too many graphical issues like low framerate or glitches. I'm pretty sure just about any PC made after 2003 would be able to run it smoothly. The movement controls are fine, but using items and performing actions seem to have a considerable lag. There were times where left-clicking a door to open it took several times for it to work.Presentation: F. As with the issues with the graphics I mentioned earlier, It doesn't seem like a lot of effort was put into this game. Although it looks like a considerable amount of people worked on this game according to the credits, this game feels like something a dev team of 3-5 people could've made in about a month. Also, it seems like most of the achievements are broken and unobtainable due to bugs. Forum members brought this up back in May 2015 and they have not been addressed as of October. So it seems like support this game has been abandoned.Overall this game is barely worth it at 19 cents and I definitely would not recommend paying full price for this title."
