,Not Recommended,291010,15603088,"Posted: 28 April, 2015",all,tamborjam,"On sale for $0.19, so well worth it to try it out, but I'm gonna have to give this a No.  I love giving horror games a fighting chance since I'm one for jump-scares and usually people giving reviews call those out as a negative thing.  As far as being scary, this game does an okay job.  The feeling of vulnerability with no weapon and the ability to lose the game by getting ""caught"" is a little nerve-racking, but otherwise, this game isn't quite there.The weapon you DO get is immediately used up.  You can't pick it up after you use it, which I find weird since it doesn't look hard to pick back up if it were real life.The Journal Pages you need to collect don't add much to the spookiness of it, and are slightly broken.  You get some voice-over for the Journal pages, but some of the pages have text and voiceover that don't match, like the voice is for a completely different page, crushing the illusion.You don't really know where to go and just hope you're going in the right direction.  No maps or anything.  This would be fine, but the scenery you get lost in is repetative, so it gets old after a while.Clicking to open things seemed un-respsonsive.  ""Click to Open"" with a hand icon on the screen, but clicking doesn't do anything unless you click like nine times.When you first get the ability to scare away shadows, it's creepy and works well.  When you encounter the Hat Man, however, you get the impression that it's supposed to work, but ends up failing, making you move too slowly to get away.I DID like how it stops you if you ""miss something"".  The game actually says ""You missed something"" if you don't pick up a vital item, which I thought was a nifty touch.Anyway, like I said, not a loss at all for 19 cents, but that's where I'd draw the line."
