,Not Recommended,291010,16391225,"Posted: 14 June, 2015",all,CrazyCanuck,"Yet another horror game where your only defenses are a flashlight, and the ability to hide.What's good about The Hat Man? Well, it looks nice. It runs well. It's short, and has both achievementsandtrading cards.The bad? Everything else. It's another typical 'try to survive with a flashlight' horror game, that takes elements from other titles without adding anything new of its own. You wander around the halls of an asylum collecting pages, and eventually a tall shadowy figure namedSlendermanThe Hat Man comes after you, slowly, so very slowly. Eventually, you'll collect enough pages to trigger the next part of the game.Acting? Atrocious. Worse than the original Resident Evil, if you can believe it. There's no difference between playing as the mother and father, aside from the voice. Even the hand icon that appears when hovering over something usable looks manly, when playing as the mother.It's supposedly based on a true story, but I can't find anything referencing the source material, other than a 'legend'. A legend is by definition something that can't be proven, so the whole ""true story"" is a misnomer.SUMMARYMm no. Not worth it. The lowest price the game has ever been is $0.19 (yes, 19 cents), so for that price, sure, why not. But the game is boring, bland, and rife with concepts that have been done long before and are long overdone."
