76561198010057570,Recommended,291010,10961626,"Posted: 29 June, 2014",all,Torn Foreskin,"Hat Man=Actually a really well made game! My first impression of the game was that once you get in to the shadow realm or whatever you want to call it, very creepy and atmospheric. Like a lot of other horror games that have been released recently, it's Slenderman essentially. Run around with the threat of a being always present and trying to kill you. That does'nt make the game boring though, don't get me wrong! The game is actually good! It has it's own little story in which you are trying to find your daughter who has ""dissappeared"". All the notes you pick up are hand written notes by your daughter which give you a really cool back story! So if you are killed by The Hat Man, (who is actually very creepy), you have that feeling of, ""Hey! I want to go back in there, and find out what happened to my daughter!"" The game is very interesting and actually makes you want to complete the game and get the story, instead of some Slender games in which you just collect the notes for the sake of getting notes. Overall I give the game a 7.5/10. Great atmosphere, the sounds are really nice and creepy, and the plot behind it makes you want more. Good game.https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IpCQAcyeJ4w&list=UUzkSzcLFfyYwG2yKZRWB_XwHere is my first video on the game. Check out the gameplay for yourself before purchasing the game. You never know!"
