76561198189224214,Recommended,291010,18021198,"Posted: 13 September, 2015",all,Viramex,"For 19 cents it isn't a bad game, especially when you can sell the cards you get from the game for more than that. This game is worth maybe $2, but I wouldn't get this game if it wasn't on sale. I like how the game sets a chilling atmosphere without being overly scary, so if you do not handle 'scary' games that well you still might want to consider getting this one.The game itself is pretty short- I think I finished it under 30 minutes, but it doesn't really seem to that much replay value. as I don't see myself replaying this in the future. The game itself isn't very original...its a horror game located in a hospital (an obvious and easy choice for a horror game), with the main objective of collecting pages (like slenderman) while getting chased by the hat man (which is not an original character). The story and characters could have been more developed as well as the lore behind the hat man and shadow people. I'm not a big fan of the 'background story getting told through a mysterious journal the main character finds' get up because I feel it is a lazy way to tell a story. But atleast there is a  somewhat coherent story which makes you feel compelled to continue the game to uncover.The graphics are eh and nothing majorly wrong with the gameplay. I didn't come across any bugs or glitches which is always good. For 19 cents you can't really go wrong."
